        <div n="235-28D-" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-235-28D--headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-28D--headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-28D--headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-235-28D--headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-28D--headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-28D--headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-235-28D--headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-235-28D--headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-28D--headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-235-28D--line-1"><hi rend="display-initial">B</hi>E<hi rend="SMALL-CAPS">NEATH</hi> this verdant <hi rend="underline">Hillock</hi> lies<hi rend="underline">Demar</hi> the <hi rend="underline">Wealthy</hi> and the <hi rend="underline">Wise</hi>.<gap/><gap/></l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-235-28D--line-2"> His <hi rend="underline">Heirs</hi>, that he might safely rest,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-235-28D--line-3"> Have put his <hi rend="underline">Carcass</hi> in a <hi rend="underline">Chest</hi>:</l><l n="4" xml:id="spp-235-28D--line-4"> The very <hi rend="underline">Chest</hi>, in which, they say,</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-235-28D--line-5"> His <hi rend="underline">other Self</hi>, his <hi rend="underline">Money</hi>, lay.</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-235-28D--line-6"> And if his <hi rend="underline">Heirs</hi> continue kind</l><l n="7" xml:id="spp-235-28D--line-7"> To that dear <hi rend="underline">Self</hi> he left behind,</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-235-28D--line-8"> I dare believe, that Four in Five</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-235-28D--line-9"> Will think his <hi rend="underline">better Half</hi> alive.235-28D-   </l></lg></div>
